{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "WorkOS Backlog Processor",
  "description": "Triggers when BACKLOG.md is saved to process tasks using instructions from CLAUDE.md with context from goals, tasks, and knowledge base",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "#CLAUDE.md\n#BACKLOG.md\n#GOALS.md\n#Tasks/\n#Knowledge/\n\nProcess the backlog following the instructions in CLAUDE.md. Important:\n\n1. Read BACKLOG.md and extract the FIRST actionable item only\n2. Use process_backlog_with_dedup to check if it's a duplicate\n3. Ask me ONE question about this item (category, priority, details, etc.)\n4. Wait for my response\n5. After I answer, process the next item\n\nWork through items ONE AT A TIME. Do not batch questions. Process item by item until the backlog is empty."
  }
}